All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
ClientPlayersHandler<T extends CustomClient>
The storage class for custom players on the client side
ClientTickable
Specifies that the CustomPlayer(sHandler) is tickable on the client-side
ClientTickPatch
Client ticks all players that implement ClientTickable
CustomClient
Effectively a CustomPlayer that does not require a serverTick method
CustomClientRegistry
The Client registry.
CustomData
The base for all custom data classes like CustomPlayer and CustomMob etc.
CustomDataHandler<I,T extends CustomData>
A handler for custom data
CustomDataRegistry<I>
Registry for CustomDataHandlers
CustomMob
The base for all custom mob data classes
CustomMobRegistry
Where mods can register their custom mobs
CustomMobsHandler<T extends CustomMob>
Handler for handling custom mobs in your mod
CustomPlayer
The base for all custom player data classes
CustomPlayerRegistry
Registry where mods can register CustomPlayers
CustomPlayersHandler<T extends CustomPlayer>
Handler for handling custom players in your mod
HUDDrawable
Specifies that the CustomPlayer is drawable on the HUD
HudDrawPatch
Draws all HUDDrawable players' HUD elements
Logger
A utility class for logging messages to the game log.
Main
This class is the ModEntry so that Necesse loads this mod.
MobLoadPatch
Loads all CustomMobs
MobSavePatch
Saves all CustomMobs
MobServerTickPatch
Ticks all CustomMobs
NeedsClientSideObject
Interface for classes that need to be sent to the client
PacketDestroyClient
Packet sent from the server to the client to destroy a client-side player.
PacketDestroyClients
Packet sent from the server to the client to destroy client-side players.
PlayerLoadPatch
Loads all CustomPlayers
PlayerSavePatch
Saves all mod's CustomPlayer data for this player.
PlayerServerTickPatch
Server ticks all players
Savable
Defines whether to save the custom data
Syncable
This interface defines that the client and server must sync their data, usually because the client needs it for client side ticking, like HUD elements.
